1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,713
[REPORTER] <i>The mastermind</i>
<i>of the La Playa Roja siege, Emil Padua,</i>

2
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:07,632
<i>has escaped after an encounter</i>
<i>that resulted in the deaths</i>

3
00:00:07,716 --> 00:00:11,010
<i>of Police Lieutenant Marlon Areza</i>
<i>and his team.</i>

4
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:12,971
<i>Let's wait for the police.</i>

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:14,639
<i>I want to be sure.</i>

6
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:18,518
<i>I want to see them arrest Greta.</i>

7
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:19,728
<i>They're here.</i>

8
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:22,814
[EMIL] <i>So you're my real boss,</i>
<i>Ma'am Greta.</i>

9
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:24,482
<i>I wish you had told me.</i>

10
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,109
<i>You've got the money.</i>

11
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,361
<i>You already got your daughter, Leni, back.</i>

12
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:30,405
<i>I still have one mission.</i>

13
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:31,489
<i>Where's my daughter?!</i>

14
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>We don't know where Ayen is.</i>

15
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:34,993
<i>You don't?</i>

16
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:38,371
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [GRETA SCREAMS]

17
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:41,624
<i>The next bullet won't just graze him.</i>

18
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:42,751
<i>I'll tell you.</i>

19
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:44,335
<i>Ayen is gone!</i>

20
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:45,795
<i>- She's dead!</i>
<i>- Greta! No!</i>

21
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,130
<i>What?!</i>

22
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:51,468
[GRETA] <i>I was just defending myself, Emil.</i>

23
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:53,136
<i>She was so furious.</i>

24
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,847
<i>I pushed her by accident.</i>
<i>She had a miscarriage.</i>

25
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,307
<i>She was going to kill me!</i>

26
00:00:57,390 --> 00:01:00,435
<i>I didn't mean to do it.</i>
<i>I didn't mean for it to happen!</i>

27
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,145
[EMIL] <i>My daughter was pregnant?!</i>

28
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,148
You didn't just kill my daughter!

29
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,025
You killed my grandchild too!

30
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,235
<i>Ma…</i>

31
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:11,529
<i>If what you're saying is true,</i>

32
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:15,241
<i>where's my daughter's body?!</i>

33
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:18,703
- [SHOVEL THUDDING, CLANKING]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

34
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:19,788
[CLINKS]

35
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:29,506
[DRAMATIC MUSIC BUILDS, THEN FADES]

36
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:37,096
Is it true that he's my son?

37
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:39,891
Huh?!

38
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:45,313
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:46,940
Homer.

40
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:50,985
What you're thinking is wrong.

41
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:54,572
I didn't use you.

42
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:59,828
I also dreamed of having
a new life with you.

43
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:07,043
- [MAN GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

44
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,337
<i>- Go on!</i>
<i>- Don't! Please don't!</i>

45
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,672
<i>- Please…</i>
<i>- Scram!</i>

46
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:12,006
<i>Let's leave!</i>

47
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:14,717
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:17,303
<i>- What's happening, Homer?</i>
<i>- Get the keys.</i>

49
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:19,055
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

50
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:25,812
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:27,939
<i>Give me that.</i>

52
00:02:29,899 --> 00:02:31,234
<i>What did you get into?</i>

53
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:34,154
<i>Wendy, this is also for us.</i>

54
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:37,699
<i>When I finally save up enough,</i>
<i>we're going to get married.</i>

55
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:43,746
[PANTING, RETCHING]

56
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:45,999
<i>Are you okay?</i>

57
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,584
<i>Huh?</i>

58
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:51,087
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

59
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:57,802
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:03,266
- Are you done?
- I am.

61
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:14,903
<i>Are you pregnant, Wendy?</i>

62
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:17,697
<i>Oh, uh, I'm not.</i>

63
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,033
<i>False alarm.</i>

64
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,204
[HOMER SIGHS]

65
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:27,665
<i>Are you sure?</i>

66
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:30,793
<i>You've been feeling nauseous for days.</i>

67
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:34,797
<i>The doctor said</i>
<i>it's because of hyperacidity.</i>

68
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:37,634
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

69
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:41,054
<i>I'm leaving for La Playa Roja</i>
<i>to accompany my boss.</i>

70
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,556
<i>I'll be away for about three days.</i>
<i>Then I'll come home.</i>

71
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:45,975
<i>Take care.</i>

72
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:48,269
<i>Take care of yourself too.</i>

73
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:52,232
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:53,524
[SMOOCHES]

75
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,151
<i>I'll get going then.</i>

76
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,489
But when I found out that
you were a criminal,

77
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:04,244
I hid my pregnancy from you.

78
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:07,830
I did it for Olsen's sake.

79
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:10,375
What if I were dragged into your crimes?

80
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:12,585
What would happen to my child?

81
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:16,756
What would happen to our child?

82
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:20,134
You admit now that Olsen is my son.

83
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:22,720
Why?

84
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:25,348
So I'll have mercy on him?

85
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,642
So I'll let him go?!

86
00:04:29,143 --> 00:04:31,187
Can you still show mercy?

87
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:34,816
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:38,486
Fathers will never abandon their children.

89
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,238
We don't leave them.

90
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:42,907
What do you know about being a father?

91
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,867
Isn't Olsen your son?

92
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,119
What did you do?

93
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:52,542
Homer?

94
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:56,921
We are not your enemy.

95
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:59,424
I didn't rat you out to the police.

96
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:03,678
I didn't kill Emil's daughter either.

97
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:08,266
Do we have to pay
for the sins of others too?

98
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:11,311
If you think about it, I'm like you.

99
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,313
I'm Greta's victim too!

100
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:18,359
She took advantage of my desperation.

101
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:21,654
Of me being poor.

102
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,324
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:25,742
I agreed to…

104
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:28,786
I agreed to take the fall for her crime

105
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:34,000
in exchange for one million pesos
to get Olsen treated.

106
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:38,337
Our son.

107
00:05:39,255 --> 00:05:41,132
I agreed to be imprisoned.

108
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:44,844
But I'm still willing
to make sacrifices for him.

109
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:48,181
For our son.

110
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:51,142
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:53,352
If you still think that

112
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:57,690
me choosing to leave you was a mistake…

113
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:06,032
then I'll accept whatever punishment
you and Emil think I deserve.

114
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:10,119
But I ask you one thing.

115
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:13,748
Don't hurt our son.

116
00:06:14,749 --> 00:06:16,793
Our son is innocent.

117
00:06:18,002 --> 00:06:19,504
Let him go.

118
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:22,048
Have mercy, Homer.

119
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:24,509
Homer, I'm begging you.

120
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:26,928
Have mercy on our son.

121
00:06:27,011 --> 00:06:33,726
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:36,062
[MOUTHING] <i>Just play along.</i>

123
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:58,543
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:36,289
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,667
- [BOTH GROANING, GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

126
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,043
<i>Brother!</i>

127
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,712
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

128
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,046
- [OLSEN] <i>Ma, don't.</i>
<i>- Stop it!</i>

129
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,673
- [OLSEN] <i>Stop!</i>
- [WENDY] <i>That's enough!</i>

130
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,717
- [SCREAMING]
- [WENDY CRYING]

131
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,055
You know, Ma,

132
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:56,225
no matter how much you beg that bastard…

133
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,895
[PANTING]

134
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:00,938
…it's useless.

135
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,565
Olsen.

136
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:05,234
I have to try. You have to try too!

137
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:06,903
Just pretend. It's the only way!

138
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,238
Ma, I already saw that devil's soul!

139
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,073
- It's the only way to--
- Ma!

140
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:14,702
We can't get out of this
by asking for mercy!

141
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:17,038
Just give it a try, Olsen!

142
00:08:17,121 --> 00:08:24,003
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PANTING]

143
00:08:24,086 --> 00:08:27,215
[OLSEN GRUNTING]

144
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:29,383
- [WENDY] What are you doing?
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

145
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:35,848
[PANTING, GROANING]

146
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:40,144
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,814
<i>But I'm still not sure</i>
<i>about him being my son.</i>

148
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,484
<i>His mother denied it, remember?</i>

149
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:48,861
<i>But if there's a chance that it's true,</i>

150
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:50,988
<i>wouldn't you prefer that?</i>

151
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:52,823
<i>Someone can finally replace Junior.</i>

152
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,202
[GAGGING]

153
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:59,330
<i>My son is irreplaceable.</i>

154
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:02,583
<i>Do you understand?! Hmm?!</i>

155
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:08,714
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:16,055
[OLSEN GROANING]

157
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:29,068
[PANTING]

158
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:30,695
[WHISPERS] Ow!

159
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:35,366
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES,
FADES]

160
00:09:35,449 --> 00:09:38,786
[SOFT DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:39,996
[WENDY] Homer.

162
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,249
I know you lost a child.

163
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:47,086
Do you want it to happen again?

164
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:53,593
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,561
[GUN THUDS]

166
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:11,319
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:14,614
And if I agree to what you want,

168
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:19,410
how can I be sure that he won't betray me?

169
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,831
I'll put my life on the line.

170
00:10:25,249 --> 00:10:26,500
[SCOFFS]

171
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:30,212
Don't tell me we're siding with them?

172
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:34,759
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

173
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:37,345
Who's our real enemy, Olsen?

174
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:42,475
The Rojas, who take advantage
of the poor and the weak?

175
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:48,147
Or them, who got exploited just like us?!

176
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:50,232
Your mother is right.

177
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:52,610
The Rojas played all of us!

178
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:56,072
Will you still stand by them?

179
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:57,865
Son!

180
00:10:57,948 --> 00:11:02,286
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:03,496
Son,

182
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:07,208
this is what I've always wanted for you.

183
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,627
A better life.

184
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,838
Together with your father.

185
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:16,092
He's finally here right in front of you.

186
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:19,845
He's finally here.

187
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:26,060
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:28,187
I can be a father to you.

189
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:31,357
I'll make it up to the both of you!

190
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:36,153
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:40,574
- [BOTH GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

192
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:41,909
- [KICK LANDS]
- [BOTH GRUNTS]

193
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:45,329
[BOTH GRUNTING]

194
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:48,874
[BANGING, THUDS]

195
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,000
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

196
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:53,879
Let's go! Let's go!

197
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,131
[WENDY GRUNTS]

198
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:56,340
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

199
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:58,968
[PANTING, COUGHS]

200
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:00,428
[SCREAMS IN PAIN]

201
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,347
[PANTING]

202
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,766
- Son, no! Don't do it!
- [SCREAMING]

203
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:09,395
Stop it! That's enough! That's enough.

204
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:12,648
Let's go.

205
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:15,734
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:21,282
[VAN ENGINE REVVING]

207
00:12:27,746 --> 00:12:31,584
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:33,169
[SEAT BELT UNBUCKLES]

209
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:34,336
Stay here.

210
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:38,174
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:40,217
[VAN DOOR UNLOCKS, OPENS]

212
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:41,427
Gwen, wait.

213
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,554
- Gwen, where's Papa? Gwen!
- [VAN DOOR CLOSES]

214
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:50,394
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:55,274
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

216
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,071
Enough!

217
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,824
No one else has to die.

218
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,284
No one…

219
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,038
except the two of you.

220
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:11,999
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

221
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:17,338
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:19,757
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

223
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,218
- [OLSEN GRUNTING]
- [KICK LANDS]

224
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:23,928
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

225
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,095
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

226
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:27,806
- [OLSEN SCREAMING IN PAIN]
- [WENDY] Olsen!

227
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:31,101
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

228
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:37,983
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,235
Ma, let's go.

230
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:41,403
[OLSEN GROANS]

231
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:50,329
[HISSING IN PAIN]

232
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:52,498
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- [OLSEN GROANS]

233
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:54,750
Come on, Ma.

234
00:13:55,584 --> 00:13:56,544
[DOOR THUDS SOFTLY]

235
00:13:56,627 --> 00:14:00,548
[PANTING, GRUNTING]

236
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:01,549
Hurry--

237
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:04,468
- Oh! [GRUNTS]
- Ma! Stand up!

238
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:11,267
[GROANING, HISSING]

239
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:17,398
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:24,321
[GUNSHOTS]

241
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,115
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

242
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:27,157
Mama, hide!

243
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:30,744
[GUNSHOTS]

244
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:37,126
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:58,355
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

246
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:11,911
[CROWBAR CLINKING]

247
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:14,288
